WEBVTT

00:10.562 --> 00:14.928
Hey everyone, I really believe that this is the time for the church to rise up.

00:14.948 --> 00:17.812
And from my perspective, that's exactly what you're doing.

00:18.392 --> 00:26.543
I can't be with you in person, but I hear of your faithfulness and I've seen the fruit of your devotion to Christ and to one another.

00:26.563 --> 00:30.148
And so I just wanna tell you that I'm proud of you and I'm praying for you.

00:30.989 --> 00:37.938
Before we get to the preaching of the word today, I wanna do something first that we always do in our services and that's the offering.

00:38.050 --> 00:43.538
And I want to acknowledge from the beginning with this that this is a difficult time financially for a lot of you.

00:43.998 --> 00:53.712
So I want to encourage you to be able to rally as community, to meet each other's needs, to take care of one another, to let your needs be known and to see the Lord provide in that way.

00:54.253 --> 00:58.038
But I also want to call you to continue to give to the church.

00:58.078 --> 01:02.004
We've adjusted our budget and we're helping more people in the church than ever.

01:02.544 --> 01:06.610
And at the Hope Center, not only are we continuing to serve meals, but

01:06.690 --> 01:09.598
We've been serving almost twice as many meals as normal.

01:09.758 --> 01:15.533
We're also supporting a lot of organizations throughout the city that serve the most vulnerable during this time.

01:16.134 --> 01:22.130
So if you want to give the best way to do that, really the only way right now is to do that through the push pay app.

01:22.210 --> 01:27.098
If you don't have that on your smartphone, then you just go to the app store, search for push pay.

01:27.218 --> 01:29.662
And then once you download the app, you search for reality LA.

01:29.702 --> 01:32.767
It's pretty easy to set up and to give in that way.

01:32.807 --> 01:40.440
And then we will pray that all that the Lord provides, that that would be used for his work and for his glory in this city.

01:41.401 --> 01:41.642
All right.

01:41.662 --> 01:46.610
If you have a Bible, go ahead and grab it and open up to Matthew chapter 14.

01:47.074 --> 01:55.066
We're doing a series right now where we are talking about how our response to this global pandemic is one of faith, hope, and love.

01:55.707 --> 02:00.995
And so what we've seen is that we wanna have a mentality, not of self-preservation, but of self-giving love.

02:01.736 --> 02:05.481
We don't need to be a people who are ridden with anxiety because we're filled with hope.

02:06.062 --> 02:09.728
And today we're gonna talk about how we're driven, not by fear, but by faith.

02:10.409 --> 02:16.658
And so I'm gonna read and preach on Matthew chapter 14, verses 22 through 33.

02:16.738 --> 02:19.080
and then I'll open our time together in prayer.

02:19.981 --> 02:22.564
Matthew chapter 14, starting in verse 22.

02:24.646 --> 02:30.371
Immediately, he made the disciples get into the boat and go before him to the other side while he dismissed the crowds.

02:31.112 --> 02:34.795
And after he had dismissed the crowds, he went up on the mountain by himself to pray.

02:35.556 --> 02:43.464
When evening came, he was there alone, but the boat by this time was a long way from the land beaten by the waves for the wind was against them.

02:44.205 --> 02:45.746
And in the fourth watch of the night,

02:45.890 --> 02:47.813
He came to them, walking on the sea.

02:48.534 --> 02:55.024
But when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were terrified and said, it is a ghost and they cried out in fear.

02:55.825 --> 03:01.414
But immediately, Jesus spoke to them saying, take heart, it is I, do not be afraid.

03:02.615 --> 03:07.323
And Peter answered him, Lord, if it is you, command me to come to you on the water.

03:07.903 --> 03:08.524
He said, come.

03:09.366 --> 03:12.791
So Peter got out of the boat and walked on the water and came to Jesus.

03:13.492 --> 03:14.834
But when he saw the wind,

03:14.978 --> 03:19.284
He was afraid, and beginning to sink, he cried out, Lord, save me.

03:20.465 --> 03:27.014
Jesus immediately reached out his hand and took hold of him, saying to him, oh, you of little faith, why did you doubt?

03:27.835 --> 03:35.064
And when they got into the boat, the wind ceased, and those in the boat worshiped him, saying, truly, you are the son of God.

03:36.045 --> 03:38.068
This is God's word, let's pray together.

03:40.171 --> 03:42.834
Lord Jesus, we pray that in this time,

03:42.946 --> 03:46.632
that we would see that you truly are the Son of God.

03:47.714 --> 03:57.051
And as we fix our eyes on you amidst all the chaos and confusion in our culture right now, we pray that it would put everything else in perspective.

03:57.932 --> 04:03.442
Lord, as your Word is preached, we pray that your Spirit would be at work in our hearts.

04:04.034 --> 04:06.337
God, would you draw the lost to yourself?

04:06.377 --> 04:08.639
Would you build up your church in this time?

04:08.719 --> 04:16.047
God, we don't want to just see the church survive, but to thrive because we believe that your spirit is at work in all of this.

04:16.668 --> 04:18.950
So God, would you have your way amongst us now?

04:18.990 --> 04:21.413
We ask this in Jesus' name, amen.

04:23.736 --> 04:33.106
Well, Martin Lloyd Jones was a Welsh medical doctor who became a preacher, and he once said this, faith is the refusal to panic.

04:34.210 --> 04:37.796
Now, panic is exactly what a lot of people in our culture are doing right now.

04:37.917 --> 04:39.219
And that's understandable.

04:39.299 --> 04:41.042
There's reason to panic.

04:41.062 --> 04:42.344
Sickness is increasing.

04:42.385 --> 04:44.088
Hospitals are overflowing.

04:44.488 --> 04:46.151
Many people have lost their jobs.

04:46.211 --> 04:49.277
A lot of people don't know how they're going to pay rent in the next couple of days.

04:49.838 --> 04:53.264
And politicians are disagreeing on the solution to all of this.

04:54.286 --> 04:57.371
And this panic then creates a culture of anxiety and fear.

04:58.092 --> 04:58.994
But let's be clear.

04:59.074 --> 05:02.518
The coronavirus didn't create a culture of anxiety and fear.

05:02.578 --> 05:06.883
No, it revealed that culture of anxiety and fear and has heightened it.

05:07.544 --> 05:13.370
So as we talk about faith today, let's remember that this isn't just a response to COVID-19.

05:13.851 --> 05:17.195
Now, this gets at the deepest longings of the human heart.

05:18.055 --> 05:23.822
And so I want to say to you as the church, we don't need to panic because we've got Christ.

05:24.523 --> 05:27.346
We can trust that He's accomplishing His purposes.

05:27.490 --> 05:29.898
We can trust that He's keeping His promises.

05:30.340 --> 05:32.828
We can trust that He's faithful to His people.

05:33.892 --> 05:40.434
And so in a society that's dominated by anxiety and fear, I want to call you to look to Christ with faith.

05:41.410 --> 05:50.743
And so let's walk through this story that I just read out of Matthew 14 and see how the word of God gives us direction in our context today as followers of Jesus.

05:51.304 --> 05:54.528
Let me just summarize a little bit of what we heard earlier.

05:55.149 --> 05:59.475
Jesus sends his disciples in a boat to go to the other side of the Sea of Galilee.

05:59.955 --> 06:02.919
And then while they're doing that, he goes up on a mountain to pray.

06:03.520 --> 06:04.361
And so they're in this boat.

06:04.402 --> 06:06.344
They're going to the other side of the Sea of Galilee.

06:06.424 --> 06:08.808
The Sea of Galilee is really a large lake.

06:08.908 --> 06:10.610
It's about four or five miles.

06:10.690 --> 06:11.391
across.

06:11.891 --> 06:15.535
And hours later, the wind is increasing.

06:15.795 --> 06:18.818
The waves start beating against the side of the boat.

06:18.838 --> 06:20.920
They find themselves in this storm.

06:21.501 --> 06:24.424
And not only are they in the storm, but it's the middle of the night.

06:24.784 --> 06:27.707
It says that they were in the fourth watch of the night.

06:28.107 --> 06:38.738
That would have been between 3 a.m. and 6 a.m. And so they would have been exhausted rowing against the waves, tired in the dark.

06:39.074 --> 06:41.939
And I want you to remember that Jesus sent them into this.

06:42.700 --> 06:50.672
And I say that because we often think that when times are difficult, that Jesus must have forgotten about us or he's taking the day off or he doesn't care.

06:50.792 --> 06:57.583
But no, Jesus actually sent them into this storm and they're being faithful to Christ in the midst of that.

06:58.324 --> 07:04.434
So there they are in the storm, but everything changes in this story when Jesus enters into the storm.

07:04.898 --> 07:09.343
and listen to their response in verse 26, as Jesus comes to them.

07:09.363 --> 07:16.210
It says, but when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were terrified and said, it is a ghost.

07:16.591 --> 07:18.933
And they cried out in fear.

07:19.994 --> 07:24.659
Now I want to pause from the story really quick to acknowledge that fear is not a bad emotion.

07:25.320 --> 07:28.904
Fear alerts us to the presence of danger or harm.

07:28.964 --> 07:32.668
And they were afraid because they didn't know who was in their midst.

07:32.728 --> 07:34.450
They thought maybe he was a ghost.

07:35.010 --> 07:36.532
but then Jesus speaks to them.

07:37.012 --> 07:43.279
And in verse 27, he says, take heart, it is I, do not be afraid.

07:44.360 --> 07:52.369
Jesus steps into the storm and it says, if he says to them, you're all right, I'm here, don't panic.

07:53.470 --> 08:00.338
Now this command that he gives them to not be afraid is actually the most common command in all of the scriptures.

08:00.642 --> 08:09.776
I mean, there's a lot of commands in the Bible, but why does God constantly command his people, do not be afraid, do not fear, take heart?

08:10.737 --> 08:14.803
I think it's because he knows that we are constantly driven by fear.

08:15.544 --> 08:20.712
We're driven by the fear of failure, by the fear of abandonment, by the fear of uncertainty.

08:20.752 --> 08:25.559
But what I love about scripture is that it doesn't just call us to not be afraid.

08:25.579 --> 08:27.602
You'll hear that all the time in our culture.

08:28.706 --> 08:34.111
In scripture, it almost always, when it calls us to not be afraid, it gives us a reason why.

08:34.131 --> 08:36.454
And that's exactly what Jesus does here.

08:37.014 --> 08:39.497
He says, don't be afraid why I'm with you.

08:39.517 --> 08:50.587
It reminds me of Psalm 23, where the Psalmist says, even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will not fear why for you are with me.

08:51.809 --> 08:57.234
And so what I want you to notice in this story is that Jesus doesn't take them out of the storm.

08:57.634 --> 09:00.177
Jesus enters into the storm with them.

09:01.499 --> 09:05.304
And we need to hear that because we always look to Christ to change our circumstances.

09:06.125 --> 09:08.949
Things are bad and we pray and we just want Him to take us out.

09:09.109 --> 09:12.474
And so our faith usually goes up and down with our circumstances.

09:13.235 --> 09:19.243
But what we're learning here is that true faith is not based on your circumstances, it's based on your Savior.

09:19.924 --> 09:21.265
And He is unchanging.

09:21.746 --> 09:22.547
He's faithful.

09:22.968 --> 09:24.690
He is with us in the storm.

09:25.186 --> 09:27.229
He doesn't just take us out of the situation.

09:27.269 --> 09:29.372
He gives us strength to get through it.

09:30.693 --> 09:33.697
And we find ourselves today in a cultural storm.

09:34.559 --> 09:35.800
You can hear the wind.

09:36.561 --> 09:40.206
You can feel the waves beating up against the side of the boat.

09:40.887 --> 09:42.930
And many of you are exhausted.

09:43.911 --> 09:49.699
And what I want you to hear today is that Jesus enters into the storm that we are in.

09:49.759 --> 09:53.644
And he speaks words of grace and mercy to us.

09:53.724 --> 09:55.026
He says to you,

09:55.330 --> 09:55.991
You're all right.

09:56.652 --> 09:57.633
I'm right here with you.

09:58.234 --> 10:00.157
Don't panic."

10:00.177 --> 10:03.281
So we need to know that Christ enters into the storm with us.

10:03.942 --> 10:05.565
But that's not the end of this story.

10:06.065 --> 10:10.191
Look at verses 28 and 29 where we see how Peter then responds.

10:10.252 --> 10:16.440
It says in verse 28, Peter answered him, Lord, if it is you, command me to come to you on the water.

10:17.141 --> 10:17.782
He said, come.

10:18.564 --> 10:23.090
So Peter got out of the boat and walked on the water and came to Jesus.

10:23.554 --> 10:26.178
Now what we have here is a picture of faith.

10:26.939 --> 10:33.970
And when the Bible talks about faith, it's a much richer and deeper idea than we often have when we think of the word faith.

10:34.551 --> 10:35.833
I would define faith like this.

10:36.033 --> 10:39.278
It's belief plus trust plus commitment.

10:39.739 --> 10:41.702
So think about how this plays out with Peter.

10:41.742 --> 10:44.847
He sees something outside of the boat in the storm.

10:44.907 --> 10:46.289
He believes something it's there.

10:46.329 --> 10:48.313
He thinks maybe it's a ghost, right?

10:48.913 --> 10:51.858
But then he speaks to it and he says, if it's you,

10:51.970 --> 10:55.234
Jesus, then command me to come to you and Jesus says, come.

10:56.015 --> 11:03.083
So then Peter moves from belief to trust because faith isn't just believing in something, it's trusting in someone.

11:03.684 --> 11:10.112
He hears Jesus' voice and he trusts, but his belief and his trust then lead him to commitment.

11:10.572 --> 11:11.513
He doesn't stay in the boat.

11:11.854 --> 11:14.777
He steps out and begins to walk to Christ.

11:15.478 --> 11:18.642
Now think about how this applies to us and our faith today.

11:19.138 --> 11:23.144
Biblical faith is not just believing that God exists.

11:23.164 --> 11:25.507
Now, even the demons believe and shudder.

11:26.388 --> 11:34.300
Biblical faith is believing, but it's also trusting God with our lives and committing to walk with him all of our days.

11:35.361 --> 11:41.911
And so look at verse 30, as the story goes on, Peter has stepped out and walking on the water to Jesus.

11:41.951 --> 11:47.058
But in verse 30, it says, but when he saw the wind, he was afraid.

11:47.522 --> 11:50.926
and beginning to sink, he cried out, Lord, save me.

11:51.486 --> 11:55.851
Now I think this is the key to the whole story, when he saw the wind.

11:57.232 --> 12:00.516
So think about it like this, when did Peter start to sink?

12:01.537 --> 12:10.246
It's when he took his eyes off of Jesus and he began to fear the waves rather than focusing on Christ, his savior.

12:11.027 --> 12:17.234
So faith, essentially, is fixing our eyes on Jesus in the midst of the storm

12:17.538 --> 12:21.622
knowing that Jesus is the author and perfecter of our faith.

12:22.443 --> 12:23.704
So let me apply this to us.

12:24.304 --> 12:25.986
Right now, we're in a storm.

12:26.967 --> 12:28.689
So what are you focusing on?

12:29.389 --> 12:30.731
We're going to have fear.

12:30.811 --> 12:36.076
Like I said before, that's a natural emotion, but the question isn't whether you will have fear.

12:36.196 --> 12:40.380
It's are you focusing on the waves or are you fixing your eyes on Jesus?

12:41.441 --> 12:46.706
Are you focusing on the problems and the obstacles and everything that could go wrong?

12:47.362 --> 12:52.631
Or are you fixing your eyes on Christ and trusting that he is faithful, no matter what?

12:53.692 --> 12:54.934
We learn that he is faithful.

12:55.315 --> 12:58.540
Look at the rest of the story, picking up in verse 31.

12:58.740 --> 13:13.204
It says, after Peter begins sinking and Christ's outlord saved me in verse 31, it says, Jesus immediately reached out his hand and took hold of him, saying to him, O you of little faith, why did you doubt?

13:14.105 --> 13:14.546
Now,

13:14.722 --> 13:17.887
Jesus shows that the heart of the matter here is faith.

13:18.628 --> 13:23.997
And for Peter, his fear of the situation was greater than his faith in the Savior.

13:24.678 --> 13:29.165
And yet Christ reaches down and rescues him.

13:29.205 --> 13:35.696
He rescues him out of the mess that he's gotten himself into because of his lack of faith.

13:36.297 --> 13:42.226
And keep going in the story in verse 32, then it says, and when they got into the boat, the wind ceased.

13:42.562 --> 13:47.207
and those in the boat worshiped him saying, truly, you are the Son of God.

13:47.948 --> 13:49.790
So think about what we've seen in this story.

13:50.311 --> 14:00.142
They went from wondering who Jesus was to being certain of his identity as the Son of God, but it was the storm that led them to that conclusion.

14:01.163 --> 14:04.687
And so as we step back from this story, here's what I want you to learn.

14:04.727 --> 14:10.514
It's safer to be in the storm with Jesus than it is to be in the boat apart from him.

14:11.458 --> 14:12.800
And we want to stay in the boat.

14:13.400 --> 14:15.102
Of course, nobody wants to be in the storm.

14:15.203 --> 14:16.264
We want security.

14:16.304 --> 14:17.906
We want to be in control.

14:17.926 --> 14:19.308
We want safety.

14:19.348 --> 14:22.732
But Jesus calls us to trust in him.

14:23.833 --> 14:26.797
And you think about the situation that we're in right now.

14:26.877 --> 14:37.650
I mean, when everything started really making a large impact culturally with the coronavirus, one of the first feelings that I had was that I'm losing control.

14:38.114 --> 14:40.758
I don't have control over my calendar anymore.

14:40.778 --> 14:43.102
I don't have control over my plans.

14:43.402 --> 14:47.048
I'm worried about if I'm going to have control over my finances.

14:47.188 --> 14:50.773
And I felt like I'm losing control, but I didn't look back on that.

14:51.494 --> 14:54.779
The control that I thought I had was an illusion to begin with.

14:55.620 --> 15:07.218
That if I'm finding control from my calendar or my bank account or from anything like that, that's just an illusion that I'm grasping onto.

15:07.714 --> 15:13.984
What we've learned in a hard way through all of this is that we don't really have control like we think that we do.

15:14.505 --> 15:16.027
And yet that's okay.

15:16.788 --> 15:23.920
Faith is embracing the fact that I'm not in control and that God is and that that is a good thing.

15:25.282 --> 15:32.413
Now this story about Jesus entering into the storm comes on his journey to the cross.

15:33.595 --> 15:35.378
And by going to the cross,

15:35.810 --> 15:41.978
Jesus entered into the storm of all the evil and wickedness and sin of this world.

15:42.699 --> 15:44.982
And he didn't just enter into it with us.

15:45.443 --> 15:46.945
He died for us.

15:47.906 --> 15:51.772
Jesus is the man of sorrows who is acquainted with grief.

15:52.192 --> 15:57.880
Why so that we might have the fullness of peace and the complete forgiveness of sins?

15:58.721 --> 15:59.642
Do you believe that?

16:00.103 --> 16:02.386
That in Christ that you have that today?

16:02.978 --> 16:07.223
See, we need faith not only to believe that God is who He says He is.

16:07.263 --> 16:11.769
We also need faith to believe that we are who He says we are.

16:11.809 --> 16:16.294
So in Christ, you are declared to be forgiven.

16:16.334 --> 16:17.996
You are secure.

16:18.076 --> 16:19.879
You are a child of God.

16:20.199 --> 16:23.964
And what you have in Christ cannot be taken from you by this world.

16:24.604 --> 16:25.425
Do you believe that?

16:26.086 --> 16:29.170
It takes faith to believe that God says,

16:29.346 --> 16:33.690
who he says that you are, who he says you are.

16:33.730 --> 16:38.555
And so Jesus entered into their storm and he said, come to me.

16:38.595 --> 16:47.884
But what I want you to hear today is that Jesus enters into your storm and he says the same thing to you, come to me.

16:47.924 --> 16:58.834
And so listen, if today you're sinking, if you're sinking in shame, if you're sinking in guilt, if you're sinking in fear and anxiety,

16:59.234 --> 17:02.940
cry out, Lord, save me and He will.

17:03.702 --> 17:09.031
Jesus reaches down and He pulls us out and He brings us to Himself.

17:10.373 --> 17:20.009
And if in the midst of this storm you're focusing on the waves, you're focusing on everything going wrong or all the potential of the situation.

17:20.049 --> 17:22.834
What I want to call you to do is

17:22.946 --> 17:33.642
not to look to the waves, but look to Christ, fix your eyes on Him, and to hear His voice saying to you, take heart in His eye, do not be afraid."

17:35.004 --> 17:47.764
Now, I ultimately want to call you to trust in Jesus, but I also want to get really practical here and talk about how this plays out for us as followers of Jesus in Los Angeles in this pandemic right now.

17:47.804 --> 17:49.426
And so we need faith.

17:49.986 --> 17:53.891
But we need faith, we need a certain kind of faith, okay?

17:53.911 --> 17:56.675
And so first of all, we need faith to lament.

17:57.776 --> 17:58.917
So think about it like this.

17:59.899 --> 18:06.888
We've gotten through this initial shock of the coronavirus and all the implications of it culturally.

18:07.368 --> 18:15.058
We're scrambling in survival mode and we're kind of settling into a new norm right now that we don't know how long it will last.

18:15.970 --> 18:23.665
But as you settle into a new norm, what I want to encourage you to do is take the time and create the space to lament.

18:23.906 --> 18:24.507
And here's why.

18:25.229 --> 18:29.698
We have all experienced an incredible amount of loss during this time.

18:30.660 --> 18:33.766
There's unmet expectations.

18:34.307 --> 18:35.890
There's a lot of disappointments.

18:36.258 --> 18:42.165
There's things in your life that you were really excited about that you were looking forward to that have been canceled or postponed.

18:42.606 --> 18:45.629
There's relationships that have been strained in all of this.

18:46.210 --> 18:49.274
We've all experienced a lot of loss.

18:49.334 --> 18:50.796
I know for me personally, I have.

18:50.836 --> 18:59.987
There's things that I'm really disappointed about, that I'm bummed, that I'm not going to get to do, that I was looking forward to over the next few months.

19:01.309 --> 19:05.714
And the appropriate response to loss is grieving and lament.

19:06.530 --> 19:09.313
to be honest with the Lord, to take that to Him.

19:10.274 --> 19:24.910
And we need to hear this as Christians because sometimes there's a temptation in the church to kind of smooth things over and put a smile on your face and act like everything's okay and pretend that we're just supposed to be positive and maybe slap a Bible verse over that.

19:25.831 --> 19:29.736
But let us remember that the Psalms are full of laments.

19:30.356 --> 19:33.560
Let us remember that we have a whole book of the Bible named after lamenting.

19:33.600 --> 19:35.442
It's called Lamentations.

19:36.098 --> 19:45.233
And let's be a people who in this time, take our loss and our grief and take it to the Lord, being completely raw and honest with Him.

19:46.175 --> 19:50.161
Lamenting is not just complaining as if we are entitled.

19:50.943 --> 19:54.589
Now, the difference between merely complaining and lamenting is faith.

19:55.831 --> 19:57.413
I believe that God is listening.

19:57.574 --> 19:59.477
I believe that God cares.

20:00.098 --> 20:02.642
I believe that He can take my heart and

20:02.882 --> 20:12.017
every emotion that I'm feeling and align it with what I believe and what I know in my mind is true that God is faithful, that God is with us, that God is at work in all of this.

20:12.798 --> 20:14.581
So we need faith to lament.

20:15.342 --> 20:18.126
Secondly, we need faith for provision.

20:18.146 --> 20:26.941
I know that for many of you right now, you don't know how you're going to pay the bills in the next couple of days as the end of the month draws near.

20:26.981 --> 20:28.984
And so you're afraid of that.

20:29.685 --> 20:30.386
And so

20:30.466 --> 20:32.670
Listen, there's a lot of things that we need to do in this.

20:32.690 --> 20:34.012
We need to work as hard as we can.

20:34.072 --> 20:36.116
We need wisdom on how to make ends meet.

20:36.536 --> 20:38.620
We need community to take care of one another.

20:38.660 --> 20:44.369
But above all, what I want to call you to is to trust God to provide.

20:45.912 --> 20:52.343
Jesus talked once about when His disciples have anxiety and worry and fear over provision.

20:52.483 --> 20:54.226
In Matthew 6, He talks about

20:54.370 --> 20:57.694
The disciples asking questions like, what are we going to eat?

20:57.794 --> 20:58.755
Or what are we going to wear?

20:58.836 --> 21:02.680
Very practical needs that they had in day-to-day life.

21:03.581 --> 21:07.426
And Jesus responds to them by saying, look at the birds.

21:07.847 --> 21:09.489
They need their sow nor reap.

21:10.009 --> 21:11.772
And yet your heavenly Father feeds them.

21:12.573 --> 21:17.278
And then he says to his disciples, are you not more valuable than they?

21:17.338 --> 21:23.506
Jesus is reminding them of God's care for them and how God will provide for them.

21:24.002 --> 21:34.356
And then he says to them what he says to us today in Matthew 633, seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness and all these things will be added to you.

21:35.178 --> 21:41.466
So I want to call you to trust in the Lord, to have the kind of faith that leads to trusting in him for provision.

21:41.566 --> 21:43.950
So we need faith to lament.

21:44.471 --> 21:46.313
We need faith for provision.

21:46.353 --> 21:50.359
And third, we need faith that serves on another.

21:51.120 --> 21:52.722
And so when I talk about faith,

21:53.026 --> 21:55.449
We're not just talking about this as individuals.

21:55.529 --> 22:00.636
There's something deeply communal about the biblical idea of faith.

22:00.656 --> 22:06.725
I think about in Mark chapter two, it tells the story about how four friends bring a paralytic to Jesus.

22:07.606 --> 22:13.594
And it says that when Jesus saw their faith, the faith of the friends, that he heals the man.

22:14.575 --> 22:19.442
And so we learn from this that faith is one of the most important attributes of a friend.

22:20.002 --> 22:23.627
And so we need the kind of faith right now that serves one another.

22:24.668 --> 22:26.610
I read an article this week by Kurt Thompson.

22:26.670 --> 22:32.378
He's a psychiatrist who is also a follower of Jesus and he's done a lot of research on anxiety.

22:33.179 --> 22:40.007
And he says this, the brain is made most anxious, not merely by the presence of a difficult or frightening situation.

22:40.047 --> 22:45.554
No, the condition that we ultimately fear is that of being abandoned.

22:46.338 --> 22:51.545
There's a lot of anxiety and worry and fear that comes along with isolation.

22:51.605 --> 22:55.050
And I want us to be able to hear this as a church.

22:56.011 --> 23:07.687
When I hear people talk about staying at home throughout the country and even in a lot of churches, for a lot of people what that means is, well, I get time at home with my family and that's bonding time and that's some of us in our church.

23:07.707 --> 23:10.731
Yes, but most of the people in our church are single.

23:11.352 --> 23:12.914
Many people live alone.

23:13.346 --> 23:30.452
And so this is a time more than ever where we have to learn to function as family, as the church, to check on each other, to pray for each other, to help each other, to get creative and showing love to one another, knowing that we are brothers and sisters in Christ.

23:31.113 --> 23:38.043
This is a time more than ever for the church to stand together, even if we're six feet apart or only connected digitally.

23:38.444 --> 23:42.610
We have to strive for the unity that we have in Christ.

23:42.690 --> 23:47.277
We need a faith that leads us to serving one another.

23:47.297 --> 23:52.083
Now, let me close by telling you one of my favorite stories.

23:52.985 --> 23:55.148
That's a story about a successful professor.

23:55.168 --> 23:56.189
He was an ethicist.

23:56.209 --> 23:57.391
His name is John Kavanaugh.

23:57.812 --> 24:00.095
He actually taught about medical ethics.

24:00.936 --> 24:03.760
And he was very accomplished throughout his career.

24:03.820 --> 24:05.202
He published a ton.

24:05.262 --> 24:06.584
He had all the accolades.

24:06.644 --> 24:10.770
He had the kind of reputation that scholars strive for.

24:11.266 --> 24:16.454
But at the end of his career, he felt empty and he didn't know what to do with the rest of his life.

24:16.534 --> 24:19.880
He had no clarity on what he should be doing.

24:20.301 --> 24:28.995
And so he thought the person to go to who seems to have all the clarity and lots of purpose in their life was Mother Teresa.

24:29.035 --> 24:35.205
And he thought, if I could just talk to Mother Teresa, then maybe I would have the kind of clarity that she has.

24:35.806 --> 24:38.610
So he literally gets on a plane, flies to India,

24:38.690 --> 24:40.132
finds Mother Teresa.

24:40.453 --> 24:45.260
And when he gets to her, she asks him, what can I do for you?

24:46.061 --> 24:48.645
And so he says, I want you to pray for me.

24:48.685 --> 24:53.031
And he specifically asks, would you pray that I would have clarity?

24:54.073 --> 24:59.521
And if you're like me, then you've prayed this prayer yourself many a time.

24:59.581 --> 25:01.303
Lord, what do you want me to do?

25:01.444 --> 25:03.387
God, if you just give me clarity.

25:03.407 --> 25:04.729
And so that was his mindset.

25:04.749 --> 25:08.434
And he asked Mother Teresa, would you pray that I have clarity?

25:08.546 --> 25:13.153
and sweet mother Teresa looks him in the eye and says, no, I will not do that.

25:14.194 --> 25:16.638
And baffled, he asks her, why?

25:16.678 --> 25:21.765
And she said this, because what you need is trust, not clarity.

25:22.787 --> 25:25.431
And she went on to say to him, I never had clarity.

25:25.751 --> 25:26.452
I had trust.

25:27.033 --> 25:28.455
And I trusted God with my life.

25:29.076 --> 25:33.002
And because I trusted him, I was free to give my life away.

25:33.062 --> 25:35.626
And we can identify with that, right?

25:36.287 --> 25:38.450
In this time of uncertainty,

25:38.690 --> 25:52.108
We feel like if I just had clarity, if I just knew when this would be over, if I just knew how I was gonna get this done, if I just knew how this was going to play out, then I would be able to walk in faithfulness.

25:53.250 --> 25:59.017
But listen, you think that you need clarity from God, but what you really need is trust in God.

25:59.778 --> 26:04.264
And what I want you to hear today is this, God is worthy of all of our trust.

26:05.346 --> 26:08.530
My question for you is not, how much faith do you have?

26:08.962 --> 26:11.906
It's, do you see how trustworthy Christ is?

26:13.068 --> 26:18.055
Because if you just obsess over your own faith, it actually begins to dwindle.

26:18.916 --> 26:22.721
But when you look to Jesus, your faith begins to swell.

26:23.743 --> 26:28.189
So church, in the midst of everything that's going on right now, don't panic.

26:29.070 --> 26:32.014
Look to Christ and keep your eyes fixed on Him.

26:32.736 --> 26:33.457
Let's pray together.

26:36.200 --> 26:37.362
Lord, we thank you.

26:38.082 --> 26:40.245
that you are worthy of all of our trust.

26:41.546 --> 26:54.742
We thank you that we can look to the cross and know that you will never let us down, that you will keep every promise that you have made and that you are with us in this storm that we find ourselves in today.

26:55.844 --> 27:07.378
We pray that you would grant us and cultivate within us the kind of faith that can lament, that can be honest with you with what we're going through right now and the loss that we've experienced.

27:08.098 --> 27:13.646
We pray, Lord, that we would have the kind of faith to cry out to you asking for provision.

27:14.127 --> 27:17.151
And God, would you provide for the needs of your people in all of this?

27:18.072 --> 27:20.836
And God, would you give us the kind of faith that serves one another?

27:21.457 --> 27:22.679
Teach us to be family.

27:23.119 --> 27:27.265
Teach us to love one another in this time in a way that's different than we ever have.

27:27.385 --> 27:29.689
God, we need you and we need one another.

27:30.269 --> 27:33.554
And so we pray that your spirit would do this work within us.

27:33.954 --> 27:41.354
Not for our glory, not for our comfort and for our safety, but for your glory and for the work that you're doing throughout this city.

27:41.655 --> 27:44.082
We pray this in Jesus name, amen.

